Garden Rescue - Series 1, Episode 8




Charlie Dimmock and the Rich brothers are in Pontefract, West Yorkshire, with Kerry, Chris and their two small children who want to live The Good Life by turning their 50-foot long plot into a place to grow their own. Added to that, they want a wildlife haven, but they want it all for a budget of just Â£2000.Both designers compete to design the garden and come up with some fabulous budget-saving tips to make the Â£2,000 go further. Charlie demonstrates how to make a bug hotel while the Rich brothers give examples of an array of plants that encourage wildlife into gardens.Plus tips on the benefits of using curved beds and ways to use colour to get a high-end designer look.
